      "id": "PopularPost153335",
      "post_content": "Am I correct in thinking that [Death's Shadow](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Death's Shadow)'s toughness will increase fast enough to prevent its demise if it is dealt exactly lethal damage at the same time as its controller is dealt damage?  \n  \nSay I have 10 life and a [Death's Shadow](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Death's Shadow), and my opponent attacks me with a [Sun Titan](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Sun Titan) (6/6) and a [Celestial Colonnade](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Celestial Colonnade) (4/4). Neither has first strike nor double strike. I block the [Sun Titan](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Sun Titan), and my 3/3 [Death's Shadow](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Death's Shadow) is dealt 6 damage at the same time as my life is reduced to 6, upping my [Death's Shadow](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Death's Shadow)'s toughness to 7 as a state-based effect at the same time as state-based effects check for lethal amounts of damage. My [Death's Shadow](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Death's Shadow) survives.  \n  \nIf so, that's amazing. This card just keeps getting better and better. Fantastic with cards that require payments of life as a \"drawback,\" fantastic as a late game comeback/finisher... [(see all)](javascript:void(0);)",
      "posted_by": "Ragamander",
      "html": "<div class=\"post evenItem\" id=\"PopularPost153335\" style=\"background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.08);\">\n<span id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl00_post\">Am I correct in thinking that <a class=\"autoCard\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Death's Shadow\">Death's Shadow</a>'s toughness will increase fast enough to prevent its demise if it is dealt exactly lethal damage at the same time as its controller is dealt damage?<br/><br/>Say I have 10 life and a <a class=\"autoCard\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Death's Shadow\">Death's Shadow</a>, and my opponent attacks me with a <a class=\"autoCard\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Sun Titan\">Sun Titan</a> (6/6) and a <a class=\"autoCard\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Celestial Colonnade\">Celestial Colonnade</a> (4/4).  Neither has first strike nor double strike.  I block the <a class=\"autoCard\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Sun Titan\">Sun Titan</a>, and my 3/3 <a class=\"autoCard\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Death's Shadow\">Death's Shadow</a> is dealt 6 damage at the same time as my life is reduced to 6, upping my <a class=\"autoCard\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Death's Shadow\">Death's Shadow</a>'s toughness to 7 as a state-based effect at the same time as state-based effects check for lethal amounts of damage.  My <a class=\"autoCard\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Death's Shadow\">Death's Shadow</a> survives.<br/><br/>If so, that's amazing.  This card just keeps getting better and better.  Fantastic with cards that require payments of life as a \"drawback,\" fantastic as a late game comeback/finisher... <a href=\"javascript:void(0);\" onclick=\"ExpandPost(event, this, 153335)\">(see all)</a></span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl00_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\"